
Overview of noun shiver

The noun shiver has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) tremble, shiver, shake -- (a reflex motion caused by cold or fear or excitement)
2. frisson, shiver, chill, quiver, shudder, thrill, tingle -- (an almost pleasurable sensation of fright; "a frisson of surprise shot through him")

Overview of verb shiver

The verb shiver has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (5) shudder, shiver, throb, thrill -- (tremble convulsively, as from fear or excitement)
